TITLE: Inflation rose 0.5% in January, more than expected and up 6.4% from a year ago
SUMMARY: The consumer price index was expected to increase 0.4% in January from a month ago and 6.2% on an annual basis, according to Dow Jones.

TITLE: Tesla board member says Musk doesn't mind bankruptcy if a rival builds a better car: 'That's his philosophy'
SUMMARY: Elon Musk remarked that he wouldn't mind Tesla going bankrupt, if it means a rival company builds a better car, according to a company board member.

TITLE: 'Think of the unthinkable': IMF chief warns world is a very different place after crises like Covid
SUMMARY: IMF Managing Director Georgieva Kristalina said that, in the "shock-prone" world we live in, people need to be more agile and "think of the unthinkable."

TITLE: Crypto markets on edge as U.S. regulatory crackdown on industry intensifies
SUMMARY: Investors are digesting a number of major regulatory actions in the U.S., as authorities look to rein in the once free-wheeling cryptocurrency industry.

TITLE: Coca-Cola revenue rises in fourth quarter, fueled by higher prices
SUMMARY: Coke said its unit case volume, which strips out the impact of currency and price changes, fell 1% in its fourth quarter.

TITLE: Ford to cut 3,800 jobs in Europe in shift to electric vehicle production
SUMMARY: Ford said it intends to cut 3,800 product development and administration jobs in Europe in the next three years.

TITLE: Singapore 2022 budget deficit set to be lower than expected; inflationary pressures persist
SUMMARY: The Singapore government will be pumping in another S$3 billion to help households cope with the rising costs of living and GST hikes.

TITLE: Nikki Haley enters race for president as first challenger to Trump for the Republican nomination
SUMMARY: Haley called for a new generation of leaders, saying Biden's record was "abysmal" and the "Washington establishment has failed us over and over and over again."

TITLE: Promoting FTX was their side hustle. Now they’re left to pick up the pieces
SUMMARY: FTX student ambassadors promoted the now bankrupt crypto exchange on their campuses to help expand it's customer base and lose funds when it collapsed.

TITLE: Japan's next central bank governor is set to be Kazuo Ueda. Here's what it means
SUMMARY: Kazuo Ueda would replace current BOJ chief Haruhiko Kuroda, who was first appointed in March 2013. His current five-year term will end on April 8.

TITLE: Shut out from their top destinations, Chinese travelers are turning to other places
SUMMARY: Visa difficulties and high-profile rows with South Korea and Japan are pushing many Chinese travelers to opt for vacations to Southeast Asia.

TITLE: China's tech giants are launching ChatGPT clones — and Beijing is watching closely
SUMMARY: Chinese technology giants from Alibaba to Baidu have announced their intentions to launch ChatGPT-style products.

TITLE: Ford to move forward with $3.5 billion EV battery plant with Chinese company
SUMMARY: Ford will own the new facility through a wholly owned subsidiary instead of operating it as a joint venture, which Ford has done with non-China partners.

TITLE: Harvard-trained psychologist: If you use any of these 8 toxic phrases, ‘your relationship is in trouble’
SUMMARY: Harvard psychologist and "Letting Go of Your Ex" author Dr. Cortney Warren reveals the toxic phrases that can destroy a relationship, and what to say instead.

TITLE: Chinese EV brand Zeekr is now worth more than Xpeng
SUMMARY: Geely-backed electric car brand Zeekr said Monday it's now valued at $13 billion after a $750 million raise from Chinese battery giant CATL and others.

TITLE: 'Fed is not your friend': Wells Fargo delivers warning ahead of key inflation report
SUMMARY: Wells Fargo Securities' Michael Schumacher believes Fed policy is working against equity investors regardless of this week's inflation data outcome.

TITLE: Chinese e-commerce giant PDD splashes on Super Bowl ad for its Temu U.S. shopping site
SUMMARY: It is rare for a Chinese firm to buy a Super Bowl ad spot, which cost millions of dollars.

TITLE: White House defends shooting down three aerial objects, despite not knowing who launched them or why
SUMMARY: The White House on Monday said it doesn't yet know what the aerial objects are that were shot down this weekend, who owns them or their purpose.

TITLE: Singapore's budget expected to focus on inflation and support for laid off workers
SUMMARY: Rising inflation and layoffs are among the concerns of Singaporeans and are expected to be addressed in the Singapore Budget 2023 on Feb. 14.

TITLE: Meta's chief business officer will leave the company after 13 years
SUMMARY: Meta's Chief Business Officer Marne Levine is stepping down after 13 years with the company, Meta announced in a release Monday.

TITLE: Shares of Palantir pop as it reports first profitable quarter
SUMMARY: Palantir's revenue for the quarter increased 18% year over year, and its U.S. commercial revenue grew 12%.

TITLE: India's largest insurer LIC says it may review stake in Adani after management meeting
SUMMARY: India's largest insurer LIC said it 'might' review its stake in Adani Group after meeting with the management.

TITLE: British semiconductor bosses threaten to move overseas as U.S. and EU splurge on chips
SUMMARY: U.K. semiconductor bosses are pleading with the government for subsidies amid fears that some chip firms will be forced to move overseas.

TITLE: Moody's cuts outlook for four Adani group companies, cites rapid declines in market value
SUMMARY: Moody's lowered its outlook for four Adani Group companies, citing a "significant and rapid decline" in the market values of the entities.

TITLE: Europe is looking to tackle sky-high debt loads after signs it will dodge a recession
SUMMARY: European officials sighed with relief Monday after new data suggested the region will avoid an economic recession.

TITLE: Ukraine plots post-war rebuilding effort with JPMorgan Chase as economic advisor
SUMMARY: One year into its conflict with Russia, which invaded Ukraine in February 2022, Ukraine's government is laying the groundwork to help rebuild the country.

TITLE: Turkey-Syria reconstruction costs to come to 'billions of dollars,' World Bank says
SUMMARY: The World Bank has slated roughly $1.8 billion of funding to Turkey and is pursuing relief aid for Syria, following last week's devastating earthquakes.

TITLE: Lidar makers Ouster and Velodyne complete their merger, creating a sector powerhouse
SUMMARY: The merger creates a lidar powerhouse with more than 850 customers and about $315 million in cash on hand.

TITLE: A big bang or a grinding assault? What to expect from Russia's new offensive in Ukraine
SUMMARY: The scope of Russia's offensive remains uncertain but whatever happens, it comes at a tricky time for Kyiv.

TITLE: Analysts see short-term strength, long-term 'generational shift' in copper prices
SUMMARY: Along with experiencing a short-term supply shortage, copper is set to undergo a "generational shift" in demand as decarbonization ramps up, according to BNY Mellon.
